choices.text: that there is not a single political party I can belong to. I have everyday problems to deal with like running the family business, bringing up my children, making my family life happy. My business has been friend shopped by my cousins. They have been supported by the top leadership and their families. Where will the royalties go? Today my business is in a very bad shape and I feel like going into depression. There is not a single problem of Kashmir or India that Kashmiri politicians have solved in past 70 years. Instead, family members of the same politicians are in the government. I am dejected with this politics. I cannot listen to the political parties when making political statements. The future of this valley is bleak. The youth will only pick up guns when they have nothing left to lose. At the moment, if the people who are running away from the valley come back and go for a fresh start, it will be transformational for everyone. However, that is not going to happen because who will make it happen. The business of Kashmir will grind to a halt if voters are scared. Kashmir will be unhealthy for investors. Kashmir needs a foreign dignitary to come from outside to get this whole Kashmir package right. A visit by a high-level functionary will mean confidence in Kashmir. In another situation, I'd like to return to Kashmir and live with a renewed hope.
